texts.text: >The battle against Baal drags on.
>Every time the Liberators try to break away and chase after Tokisada,
>they were immediately chased down and dragged into another fight.
Shit! This guy just won't let go!
We'll never be able to catch Tokisada like this!
Baal.
The time has come. You can withdraw now. Leave these humans be.
...As you wish.
What the...!
>Baal promptly disappears.
Why that coward... He dogged us all this time and he just ran away?
But now we're free to look for Tokisada!
The thing is, we have no idea where to look...
That's not a problem, I know where he is.
He's grown so powerful that I can sense him even from this distance...
We have to hurry!
This way. His power is immense.
Here! The other side of this gate!
>The Liberators burst through the gate
>only to see Tokisada at the feet of an unfamiliar demon.
Ugh... Impossible...
Ah yes, this will do just fine.
This should be enough power to satisfy his eminence.

Give it back...!
I gathered all that power...
What the hell's goin' on here?
Wait. Tokisada no longer has that immense power...
It's all centered on that demon now.
Yes, you are correct. The power that Tokisada amassed
and that of his own, is now all mine.
Damn you to Hell, you... Godless demon...
That demon... I've never seen him, but I can recognized that voice anywhere.
It's that voice from the heavens.
If he's God's messenger, he sure doesn't look it.
What? Impossible!
Well of course it was all a sham. You didn't actually believe all that, did you?
But first, let me introduce myself. I am the demon lord Lucifuge.
A demon lord? You deceived me?
Ah, you accuse me of deception,
but you are the one that believed in an unknown voice that only spoke honeyed words,
are you not?
So my resurrection... And fighting for God...
Oh dear. You are still oblivious to the truth. How can one be so blind?
This world where only you can slay demons and absorb their power...
It was created by you, Tokisada.
It was created out of your intense anguish and desire.
This world was willed into existence by Tokisada...?
Wait, could this be the Aura's...?
I know this because I now hold your original power in my hand.
I can read you like a book, and the chapters are filled with anguish and regret.
You were used by all the samurai who wanted to overthrow the Shogunate.
They made up stories of you performing miracles
and made you their figurehead...
but you had neither the brains nor the brawn to be a military leader, did you?
You must have despaired when you saw the people that followed you into battle because they had faith in you get massacred.
In your despair, did you not curse God for not coming to your aid?
Did you not curse the cruel and tyrannical Shogunate government officials? Did you not curse Man?
You didn't though, did you? Even after everything that happened,, you still believed in God.
You could not forsake your faith, so you chose to bear the cross of that tragedy all on your own.
Instead of cursing God or Man, you cursed yourself for being powerless.
You continued to do so even centuries after your death, and that's what created this place.
It's a sad thing really. You continued to thirst for power
without knowing that the human world has changed with the passage of time.
What did you say?
I... I thought if I had the power, I could make everything right.
I thought I could save the people from their suffering...
If what you tell me is true, then...
What was the point... All this time I...
Tokisada...
Ah, but there is a point. The power you've amassed will be given as a tribute
to one who is as powerful as God Himself...
Or should I say... To his eminence who will one day overpower God and enslave all.
Huh? Who are ya talkin' about?
I am not compelled to answer. In any case, I have no more use of this world.
I came with only the intention of observing the anomaly that created it,
but was able to obtain a nice gift to his eminence. This was a most fruitful endeavor.
I will show mercy to the master of this world by leaving peacefully.
After all, he has but moments to live. He may spend it wallowing in self pity if he wants.
>With that, Lucifuge vanishes...
Wait!! Shit... What the hell man...
Ugh...
Tokisada!
>Tokisada collapses
>He looks like he's going to dissipate at any moment...

Please... Listen to my confession.
No, my excuse...
...Alright. We're listening.
I was used as a figurehead during the rebellion to draw and bind people to the cause.
I knew that... I wasn't stupid.
Me myself, I was nothing. Just a boy who believed in God.
But even so, I fought for God...
I fought to protect my faith. That part was true.
That's why I hated myself for being so powerless. I kept telling myself...
that I could've done something, if I only had the power...
That I could've saved those who put their faith in me and in God.
That's why you sought power...
But it would seem that all that was in vain.

...
I'll tell you this much...
In today's world, a lot of people believe in God.
Without fear of persecution.
I see... That sounds like a wonderful age to live in.
If... If there is a next life...
If a fool like me could get another chance at life,
I hope I won't mess it up.
I apologize for all the trouble I have caused... Please forgive me for my trespasses upon you...
>Tokisada's visage becomes distorted
>as he fades completely out of existence...
>The surrounding area is wrapped in darkness, but gradually becomes brighter.
Is this... The real world?
According to Lucifuge, that place was created by Tokisada.
I think that's why it dispersed when its creator died.
...And now the Aura Gate is all back to normal again.
So, case closed I guess?
Though nothing about that felt resolved at all....
Yes...
And not just because of Tokisada's tragic end,
but also because of the existence of this "his eminence" Lucifuge kept referring to.
Could it be that there is some mastermind behind Lucifuge pulling the strings?
And if that's true, would this mastermind be a threat to mankind...?
That raises so many question.
Whadda ya think, Shionyan?
Yo, Shionyan?
Oh, sorry. I was just thinking about what happened to Tokisada.
Yo, you gettin' all sentimental on me now? That ain't the Shionyan I know.
Hey Megakin, that was uncalled for.
Jerk.
...No, I'm not being sentimental.
It's just that the incident with the Asuras and this case with Tokisada
both involved the appearance of unprecedented special Aura Gates.
So that's one similarity between these cases.
I was just trying to remember if there were any others.
If we can find out what's triggering this phenomenon, we might be able to know when it will happen again and how to deal with it.
Oh, I never thought of that! You ARE the brains of this operation!
Wait, you're the Aura Gate expert. Shouldn't you be the first one to notice things like this?
No, I think YOU'RE the right person for the job!

*Sigh*
Seiran...
Alright, no more jokes. Yes, I know this is something I'm going to have to look into.
That's two incidents in a row now, it can't be a coincidence.
But other than that, thanks for the help as usual everyone!
Say, are you guys hungry? Let's go get some ramen, my treat.
You know what they say, you can't fight on an empty stomach. C'mon, let's go!
